{{Cleanup FJC Bio}}
'''Reginald C. Lindsay''' (born 1945) is a [[United States federal judge]].

Lindsay was born in [[Birmingham, Alabama]]. He received a [[B.A.]] from [[Morehouse College]] in 1967. He received a [[Juris Doctor|J.D.]] from [[Harvard Law School]] in 1970. He was in private practice of law in [[Boston, Massachusetts]] from 1970 to 1975. He was a State commissioner of public utilities, Massachusetts from 1975 to 1977. He was in private practice of law in [[Boston, Massachusetts]] from 1977 to 1993. 

Lindsay was a federal judge to the [[United States District Court for the District of Massachusetts]]. Lindsay was nominated by President [[William J. Clinton]] on October 27, 1993, to a seat vacated by [[David Sutherland Nelson]]. He was confirmed by the [[United States Senate]] on November 20, 1993, and received commission on November 24, 1993. 

